<div class="section">Key developments &#8212; past 12 hours (23 Mar 18:00 to 24 Mar 09:00 UTC+2)</div>
<div class="g2">
  <div class="dev-card">
    <div class="dev-top"><span style="font-size:14px">&#127968;</span><span class="dev-label">Netanyahu at White House — 24/25 Mar summit</span><span class="dev-status ds-green">Most significant diplomacy of the war</span></div>
    <div class="dev-body">
      <b>Netanyahu flies to Washington (24 Mar):</b> Summit at US State Department starts today, concludes at White House 25 Mar. Netanyahu video statement: "Trump believes there is an opportunity to leverage our achievements to realize the goals of the war through an agreement that will safeguard our vital interests."<br>
      <b>Multi-party framework:</b> Turkey FM Fidan + Iran FM Araghchi + US Witkoff met. Parallel talks: Ankara, Riyadh, Doha, Oman, Pakistan, Egypt. Goal: de-escalation, ceasefire, broader political settlement. Diplomats: "This may be the final opportunity."<br>
      <b>Trump:</b> Iran "called" to start talks. "They want to make a deal." Key goal: no nuclear weapons for Iran. "I think Israel will be very happy with what we have." If deal fails by 28 Mar (5-day pause expiry), analysts warn region faces significant hostility spike.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="dev-card">
    <div class="dev-top"><span style="font-size:14px">&#9992;&#65039;</span><span class="dev-label">Lufthansa extends to October · Iraq airspace closed</span><span class="dev-status ds-red">Longest European carrier extension to date</span></div>
    <div class="dev-body">
      <b>Lufthansa (NEW 23 Mar):</b> Dubai and Tel Aviv suspended to <b>31 May 2026</b>. Abu Dhabi, Beirut, Tehran suspended to <b>24 October 2026</b>. First major European carrier to plan explicitly for months-long disruption. Bloomberg confirmed (Times of Israel 23 Mar).<br>
      <b>Iraq airspace:</b> Extended closure through Wednesday 25 Mar minimum. Kuwait filed ICAO protest over Iranian airspace violations at airport facilities.<br>
      <b>UK air defence:</b> UK sending short-range air defence systems to Middle East to counter Iranian missile attacks (Starmer confirmed 23 Mar). Britain also summoned Iran&#x27;s ambassador over hostile surveillance on London&#x27;s Jewish community.<br>
      <b>EASA CZIB:</b> Still not renewed as of 24 Mar morning. Ben Gurion operating under PPR.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="dev-card">
    <div class="dev-top"><span style="font-size:14px">&#128308;</span><span class="dev-label">Iran attacks continue alongside talks</span><span class="dev-status ds-amber">Dual track — attacking and negotiating simultaneously</span></div>
    <div class="dev-body">
      <b>Iran overnight (23&#8211;24 Mar):</b> Attacks on Israel and Gulf states continuing at reduced tempo. Sirens in northern Israel. West Bank missile debris confirmed (Pedu&#x27;el settlement). 70th wave of attacks against Gulf states ongoing. Iran publicly denying any talks with US.<br>
      <b>Lebanon (Al Jazeera 24 Mar):</b> 1,039 killed and 2,876 wounded in Lebanon since 2 Mar Israel expanded offensive. 10 deaths and 90 injuries in past 24hrs. IDF struck Qasmiyeh Bridge overnight (Hezbollah logistics).<br>
