    <div class="dev-body">
      <b>IDF confirmation (23 Mar):</b> Ofer Moskovitz (Misgav Am, 22 Mar) killed by IDF&#x27;s own artillery &#8212; not Hezbollah. Northern Command Maj. Gen. Milo investigation concluded: "severe issues and operational errors in planning and execution." Artillery fired at incorrect angle. Did not follow required protocols. First confirmed IDF friendly fire civilian death of the conflict.<br>
      <b>Pope Leo XIV (23 Mar):</b> Sharply criticised aerial bombardments as indiscriminate, saying they "should have been banned forever." First US pope Leo did not name the conflict but called for ceasefire. "No one should have to fear that threats of death and destruction might come from the sky."<br>
